WEBVTT

00:02.818 --> 00:05.942
All together as a church family, we all got to worship together in that song.

00:06.082 --> 00:08.265
And I am just so honored to be with you in this moment.

00:09.066 --> 00:10.387
God's presence is good.

00:10.728 --> 00:15.654
Hey, we have gathered today in the presence of a good God.

00:15.714 --> 00:19.439
Can I get an amen at church to the highlands today?

00:19.459 --> 00:20.700
He is rich in mercy.

00:20.740 --> 00:23.764
He is full of love and power and strength.

00:23.784 --> 00:26.047
We are here together in his presence.

00:26.087 --> 00:27.929
I'm so excited for these next nine weeks.

00:28.030 --> 00:29.832
I believe God has so much in store for us.

00:30.352 --> 00:31.634
And I just want to kick us off.

00:31.778 --> 00:38.448
with an incredible verse, Psalm 34.8 says, Oh, taste and see that the Lord is good.

00:39.749 --> 00:41.812
Bless is he who takes refuge in him.

00:41.832 --> 00:47.100
And so I grew up in the church, maybe you did as well, where the pastor, almost every week would do this deal.

00:47.140 --> 00:49.463
He would say, God is good and we would all say all the time.

00:49.864 --> 00:51.827
And then he would say all the time, God is good.

00:51.967 --> 00:53.068
I'm bringing it back today.

00:53.970 --> 00:54.510
Are you all ready?

00:54.651 --> 00:55.131
Are you ready?

00:56.253 --> 00:56.453
All right.

00:56.473 --> 00:57.214
God is good.

00:58.416 --> 00:59.858
And all the time.

01:00.034 --> 01:01.136
Oh, come on, one more time.

01:01.156 --> 01:01.857
God is good.

01:02.818 --> 01:06.084
And all the time, put your hands together if you believe it today.

01:06.124 --> 01:07.005
He's a good God.

01:08.087 --> 01:08.748
Praise God.

01:11.152 --> 01:14.216
And the last part of that verse is perfect to tee us off into this series.

01:14.717 --> 01:17.001
It says, blessed are those who take refuge in Him.

01:17.021 --> 01:22.770
So it's one thing to know that, and as you already heard your campus pastors share, we want to experience His goodness.

01:22.850 --> 01:30.341
And I think there's a moment of decision, even at the beginning of the message today, in the beginning of this series, where we just say, God, if you are good, we want to taste and see it.

01:30.361 --> 01:31.963
We want to take refuge in you.

01:31.983 --> 01:33.826
So I want to pray for us in this moment.

01:33.846 --> 01:42.719
I think this is actually a significant moment, whether you're here for the first time, whether you know God personally or not, even following Him for years, wherever you are in your faith journey.

01:43.180 --> 01:47.666
This is a moment for all of us to say, God, if you have something for me out, I want to taste

01:47.970 --> 01:50.896
And see, I'm choosing to take refuge in you.

01:50.936 --> 01:54.542
It's a moment for us, really a faith moment for us to put our lives in his hands.

01:55.003 --> 01:55.945
I would love to pray for us.

01:56.045 --> 01:58.250
As I do, would you just do that in your own heart, God, right now?

01:58.290 --> 02:01.035
We choose to take refuge in you.

02:01.776 --> 02:03.840
We just declared it, you are a good God.

02:04.461 --> 02:07.707
And we want to experience that, to taste and see it in our own lives.

02:07.748 --> 02:11.154
And we know the only way to do that is really to give you permission.

02:11.746 --> 02:13.649
An act of faith to say, God, come have your way.

02:13.729 --> 02:17.834
Speak to us, mold us, shape us, change us wherever we're out of alignment.

02:17.854 --> 02:18.736
Bring us into alignment.

02:18.756 --> 02:23.482
We want to experience your mercy, your grace, your truth, everything you have for us, we want it today, God.

02:24.003 --> 02:27.327
We have come to church to meet with you today, God.

02:27.347 --> 02:30.672
And we just say one more time, you're a good God in Jesus' name.

02:30.732 --> 02:32.354
Everybody said, amen.

02:32.374 --> 02:35.939
Put your hands together one more time just to celebrate a good God.

02:37.842 --> 02:38.002
Awesome.

02:38.786 --> 02:41.071
All right, well, I'm excited to get into the Word of God.

02:41.091 --> 02:43.977
Before that high five, your neighbor, you can have a seat at every location.

02:50.391 --> 02:55.282
It is a great day to be in church, and you've heard all about it to this point.

02:55.490 --> 02:57.232
We are starting a brand new series.

02:57.272 --> 02:59.675
If you have your app out, I would love you to open it.

02:59.695 --> 03:01.497
There's a chance for you to take message notes there.

03:02.058 --> 03:05.122
If you don't have it and you want to take notes, it's a great day really just to lean in.

03:05.162 --> 03:09.467
This whole series, even that field God has room for you to jot down some notes today.

03:09.527 --> 03:17.316
But I want to start out the entire series with a question, and this is the question we're going to answer today that's really going to open a doorway up to the next eight weeks.

03:17.877 --> 03:22.002
And here's the question, and again, it's in your app if you want to start there, is how do we know

03:22.338 --> 03:22.979
God is good.

03:23.339 --> 03:24.801
So we're gonna teach this series.

03:25.001 --> 03:26.903
We just said, God is good all the time.

03:27.384 --> 03:34.852
The question that I think is appropriate and I wanna answer today from the word of God is, okay, I hear you preacher, but how do we know that?

03:35.392 --> 03:36.594
How do we know it in our hearts?

03:36.634 --> 03:37.915
How do we know it in our minds?

03:38.456 --> 03:41.119
How do we know God is good?

03:41.179 --> 03:45.083
And so where we're gonna start today is where we always start at Church of the Highlands.

03:45.944 --> 03:47.946
The Bible proclaims the goodness of God.

03:47.986 --> 03:49.528
Can I get amen for the word of God?

03:49.788 --> 03:51.410
Okay, so we're always gonna start.

03:51.586 --> 04:02.343
in the Bible, and that's where we're gonna start for this whole series, is that the Bible, over and over, from Genesis to Revelation, verse after verse, proclaims his goodness.

04:02.964 --> 04:05.228
And many of those verses are found in the book of Psalms.

04:05.248 --> 04:10.075
There's so many examples in Psalms where it just talks about David and others, talk about the goodness of God.

04:10.095 --> 04:11.798
We just read this when I wanna come back to it.

04:12.279 --> 04:16.866
Psalm 34, eight, oh, taste and see that the Lord is good.

04:17.367 --> 04:19.410
And again, blessed are those who take refuge

04:19.682 --> 04:25.711
And what I love about this, and it really frames our theology of God, God doesn't just do goodness.

04:25.731 --> 04:31.879
So when we think about God, it's not like this kind of Santa Claus figure that, you know, does good or he gives out these gifts or it's all random.

04:31.980 --> 04:33.342
God doesn't just do goodness.

04:33.362 --> 04:34.383
He is goodness.

04:35.304 --> 04:37.407
The scripture says the Lord is good.

04:37.608 --> 04:38.229
He is good.

04:38.289 --> 04:38.890
He is good.

04:39.951 --> 04:41.814
And what I love about that is that he can't be ungood.

04:41.834 --> 04:44.818
In fact, Psalm 92 says that the Lord is upright.

04:44.898 --> 04:45.559
He is my rock.

04:45.579 --> 04:47.602
There is no wickedness in him.

04:48.322 --> 04:54.070
So the Lord is good and he, I don't think that's even actually a word, but in Alabama and Georgia, it's a word, he can't be ungood.

04:55.291 --> 04:56.813
There is no wickedness in him.

04:57.574 --> 04:58.816
Hey church, that's really good news.

04:59.196 --> 05:01.920
The Lord is good and there is no wickedness in him.

05:02.020 --> 05:04.984
He doesn't have bitterness or envy or he doesn't lie or cheat.

05:05.024 --> 05:06.366
He cannot be unjust.

05:06.646 --> 05:11.492
And when you use that word can't next to God, the only time we have permission to do that is when God does it himself.

05:12.233 --> 05:14.176
And he's the one that says, there is no wickedness in me.

05:14.957 --> 05:15.858
I am a good,

05:16.130 --> 05:24.402
Psalm 23, 6, Psalm 23, what a beautiful, maybe the most beautiful of all the Psalms, where David's just reflecting on God as our shepherd.

05:24.823 --> 05:27.907
Psalm 23, the verse six says, surely, we just sang about this.

05:28.128 --> 05:32.414
Surely your goodness and love will follow me all the days of my life.

05:32.735 --> 05:33.836
Let's say that word, surely.

05:34.998 --> 05:36.019
That's a good faith word.

05:36.740 --> 05:37.582
Surely, I know it.

05:37.622 --> 05:38.183
It's in my heart.

05:38.263 --> 05:43.250
I know that your goodness is following after me, and I'm gonna dwell in the house.

05:43.586 --> 05:44.487
of the Lord forever.

05:44.547 --> 05:47.671
I just love the thought that God's goodness is generous.

05:47.691 --> 05:49.654
He's generous with His goodness.

05:49.674 --> 05:50.595
He doesn't withhold it.

05:50.935 --> 05:52.076
He's not stingy with it.

05:52.577 --> 05:54.920
He is a generous, good God.

05:54.940 --> 05:55.781
Come on, God is good.

05:55.821 --> 05:59.426
And all the time, God is good.

05:59.486 --> 06:01.128
He's a good God.

06:01.728 --> 06:03.110
And so the Bible proclaims it.

06:03.671 --> 06:05.173
And here's the next thing I want to reflect on.

06:05.213 --> 06:06.975
And this is huge.

06:07.275 --> 06:10.960
In fact, there's a big theology, kind of big idea about God in this statement.

06:10.980 --> 06:12.722
And that is this, all of humanity.

06:13.154 --> 06:14.617
has experienced the goodness of God.

06:15.839 --> 06:20.127
So the idea here is actually, again, theologically called common grace.

06:20.327 --> 06:21.650
Our God is such a good God.

06:21.690 --> 06:25.657
It's not just that He's good to a certain group of people, that He is good to all people.

06:25.938 --> 06:29.905
Everyone who has ever lived has experienced the goodness of God.

06:30.005 --> 06:32.690
Jesus actually teaches us during the Sermon on the Mount,

06:32.834 --> 06:43.405
The most important, longest recorded sermon and most important sermon, while Jesus was ministering on earth, in Matthew chapter five, verse 45 says, he causes the sun to rise on the evil and the good.

06:44.006 --> 06:47.290
He sends rain on the righteous and the unrighteous.

06:47.310 --> 06:48.251
That's common grace.

06:48.931 --> 06:58.922
That our God is a good God and all of humanity have experienced his goodness, which means, of course, to everyone in the sound of our voice right now has experienced the goodness of God.

06:58.942 --> 07:00.924
So I want us to think about it for a moment.

07:00.944 --> 07:02.386
In fact, even in the middle of the service,

07:02.658 --> 07:04.802
I've been thinking about this reflecting on it, but I want you to.

07:05.383 --> 07:08.309
When you think about the goodness of God, what comes to mind?

07:09.571 --> 07:11.235
Like right now in this moment, what comes to mind?

07:11.255 --> 07:15.984
When you think about His goodness, when you think about His grace, when you think about His love, what is it that comes to mind?

07:16.485 --> 07:19.270
For me, immediately I think about my family.

07:19.290 --> 07:21.234
I got a picture of my crew here, Jill.

07:21.314 --> 07:22.777
who's on the front row, my four boys.

07:22.897 --> 07:26.082
This is a picture that for us as an environment we love.

07:26.102 --> 07:27.685
We're out in the great outdoors.

07:27.705 --> 07:30.089
We're at a national park in Montana called Glacier.

07:30.450 --> 07:31.552
We've just hiked this trail.

07:31.572 --> 07:32.714
We're in this beautiful place.

07:32.734 --> 07:34.757
Y'all, that water was freezing cold right after this.

07:35.158 --> 07:36.300
We all took a cold plunge.

07:36.360 --> 07:38.904
It was all the things we love kind of wrapped into one.

07:38.925 --> 07:39.606
And here's what I know.

07:39.986 --> 07:41.529
Our family is not perfect.

07:41.549 --> 07:42.391
We got a long way to go.

07:42.411 --> 07:46.738
We were in the trenches with all of you, but I don't deserve my family, my amazing wife.

07:47.042 --> 07:48.103
my boys, our health.

07:48.183 --> 07:50.185
I mean, I am so grateful to God.

07:50.205 --> 07:51.726
Can anybody love your family out there today?

07:52.027 --> 07:52.767
I'm blessed.

07:52.827 --> 07:57.412
We've got to think about what comes to mind when you think about God's goodness.

07:57.792 --> 08:00.835
I've got to say this next one, and not just because I'm here on stage.

08:00.855 --> 08:03.577
When I think about the goodness of God, I think about Church of the Highlands.

08:04.238 --> 08:07.461
And I showed a graphic last week at Vision Sunday that I want to come back to.

08:07.501 --> 08:12.005
This just shows the footprint, the geographical footprint of our church.

08:12.065 --> 08:17.010
Those darker dots are physical locations, and the lighter ones are the correctional facilities.

08:17.282 --> 08:18.544
Y'all, that is a miracle.

08:18.564 --> 08:20.807
That represents thousands of people.

08:21.348 --> 08:25.093
God is a good God that He has brought all of us together in one church.

08:25.113 --> 08:26.415
I got like one person clapping over here.

08:26.435 --> 08:28.037
You put your hand, you're going to clap a lot today.

08:28.518 --> 08:29.960
We're talking about the goodness of God.

08:31.462 --> 08:34.085
And the fact that God would be moving in our church is such a miracle.

08:34.125 --> 08:38.672
And especially in the area of our young people, y'all do know that Highlawn's kids is not just childcare.

08:38.692 --> 08:43.378
I am grateful that we got to drop our kids off on the way to church today.

08:43.522 --> 08:44.023
Anybody?

08:44.043 --> 08:44.944
Okay, okay, that's great.

08:45.285 --> 08:46.727
But y'all, we have dream teamers in there.

08:46.767 --> 08:48.329
Our dream team, our amazing dream teamer in there.

08:48.349 --> 08:49.631
They're ministering to our kids right now.

08:49.671 --> 08:51.855
Kids fall in love with Jesus at a young age.

08:51.875 --> 08:52.576
I'm grateful for that.

08:52.596 --> 08:53.598
That's the goodness of God.

08:54.098 --> 09:01.770
I mean, Hylen's kids' environments, walking in those environments and just hearing young kids, you know, second grade, third grade, even younger, worshiping our God.

09:01.850 --> 09:02.732
God's a good God.

09:02.812 --> 09:06.998
And God's moving in our high school students, our middle school students, even in our college students.

09:07.439 --> 09:09.522
This past summer at motion conference,

09:09.794 --> 09:12.357
It was just such a powerful, it was different.

09:12.377 --> 09:16.942
It's always good, but it was just a spirit of God there that I've never felt before.

09:16.962 --> 09:25.132
17,000 students in one arena, I mean, the stage was in the center, and in the very last session, we do this kind of moment.

09:25.372 --> 09:32.360
It's really the decision moment for the whole conference, and where we ask students to write down just the decision they're making as they walk out of that place.

09:32.780 --> 09:34.322
We call it me plus motion.

09:34.498 --> 09:42.528
And this year, we were teaching on Isaiah 6, and it was the idea of, here I am, send me God, I'm yours, use me, I'm your hands and feet.

09:42.868 --> 09:45.331
And we were having students write that down and put the picture up on the screen.

09:45.711 --> 09:49.976
This one young man in the middle of all that, it was completely quiet, no keys, no music.

09:49.996 --> 09:56.364
This one young man stands up in the middle of the arena and goes, I will go, he shouts it out, and it reverb around the entire arena.

09:57.205 --> 10:01.490
And when I think about the goodness of God, I think about that moment this year.

10:01.922 --> 10:08.173
and just seeing right after that, all 17,000 students standing up saying, I'm gonna live for Jesus.

10:08.253 --> 10:09.095
Come on, somebody.

10:09.555 --> 10:10.777
Our God is a good God.

10:12.721 --> 10:18.751
And I also think about, and I know that this is on your list as well, I think about all the things that should have taken me out over the years.

10:18.852 --> 10:23.640
I mean, the mistakes that I've made, the dumb thing, anybody out there ever done some dumb stuff, you should not be living, breathing right now.

10:24.381 --> 10:25.964
Your boy on stage right now, I'm one of those.

10:26.044 --> 10:27.186
I mean, so many times,

10:27.362 --> 10:31.647
that I just messed up and it was only by the grace and goodness of God that I made it through that situation.

10:31.927 --> 10:48.987
The immediate one I thought about, I haven't thought about this in years, I was 17 years old, I was about this time of year, I left football practice, I went to church that evening, we had church on Thursday night, and then after that I went to my girlfriend's house at the time, and we did what everybody in the 90s did, we watched Dawson's Creek, okay, that's what we did that night.

10:49.487 --> 10:55.474
And if you're a little bit older than me, you watched 90210, come on, if you're younger than me, it was One Tree Hill,

10:56.066 --> 10:57.588
And then all of us watched Family Matters.

10:57.808 --> 10:59.651
Urkel forever, right?

10:59.671 --> 11:00.231
Urkel forever.

11:00.251 --> 11:03.796
So we watched that show and we walked out to the car and I'm not proud of this.

11:03.816 --> 11:05.298
It's such a, so dumb.

11:05.338 --> 11:09.804
And in this story changed my life forever, but there was, I was inconsistent back then wearing my seat belts.

11:09.904 --> 11:12.547
So dumbest thing ever, but that's just the truth of what it was.

11:12.647 --> 11:17.173
And my girlfriend at night looked at me and she said, put on your seat belt and I put my seat belt on.

11:17.814 --> 11:18.956
I drove halfway home.

11:19.076 --> 11:20.177
It was about a 45 minute drive.

11:20.237 --> 11:21.539
I stopped at a shell station.

11:21.599 --> 11:22.440
Come on in the small town.

11:22.460 --> 11:23.922
You just call it the shell station.

11:24.546 --> 11:27.850
It's not A-shell station, it is the shell station.

11:28.110 --> 11:30.193
Next to the pigly wiggly, right?

11:30.674 --> 11:32.015
Next to the dollar general.

11:32.276 --> 11:33.557
That's my life.

11:33.617 --> 11:39.044
So I stopped there and every night, you know, because you're 17, your metabolism's in a different situation.

11:39.745 --> 11:41.146
Oh, you're 17-year-olds, just wait.

11:41.607 --> 11:44.410
But I would grab a Dr. Pepper and a bag of Doritos.

11:44.430 --> 11:50.578
11 o'clock at night, crushing a Dr. Pepper is not, that is not 64 grams of sugar.

11:51.810 --> 11:52.551
I did research.

11:52.611 --> 11:55.635
That's the same as five Krispy Kreme donuts.

11:57.517 --> 12:00.060
That's a whole other level, right?

12:00.080 --> 12:00.981
And I bagged Doritos.

12:01.001 --> 12:02.283
That was just my flow for whatever reason.

12:02.323 --> 12:04.926
I mean, 11 o'clock at night drinking Dr. Pepper, then go to sleep.

12:04.986 --> 12:06.769
That's 17 years old in a nutshell right there.

12:07.309 --> 12:10.233
But 10 minutes after that, I haven't finished my Dr. Pepper yet.

12:10.273 --> 12:11.154
I'm coming over a hill.

12:11.635 --> 12:13.277
I'm in a little Dodge neon compact.

12:13.317 --> 12:14.258
My mom's car.

12:14.434 --> 12:23.779
A crown Victoria, y'all know that, a huge, but it was a station wagon, comes over the hill going 70, they estimate 70 to 75 miles an hour, hits me head on hydroplanes, hits me head on.

12:24.440 --> 12:27.729
The car starts spinning, I'm down in a ravine, Dr. Pepper everywhere.

12:28.611 --> 12:31.218
When I smell Dr. Pepper, that's what I remember, airbags out.

12:31.458 --> 12:34.642
I'm just, I'm in a complete state of shock.

12:34.722 --> 12:37.785
I mean, the side window, I couldn't open the door because of the damage.

12:37.825 --> 12:38.987
The side window, I bust it out.

12:39.287 --> 12:40.168
I climb out the side window.

12:40.188 --> 12:43.392
For whatever reason, I remember my dad telling me if I was in an accident, make sure they don't leave.

12:43.712 --> 12:46.555
So I start chasing the guy down after that accident.

12:46.575 --> 12:47.456
He's not going anywhere.

12:47.977 --> 12:51.060
And I woke up the next morning, I drove by where it happened, and I saw the car.

12:51.200 --> 12:53.924
I should not have walked out of there alive.

12:54.704 --> 12:59.570
When anybody got a story about the goodness of God, I mean, I just, I shouldn't be standing here.

13:00.962 --> 13:02.644
So what do you think of when you think about His goodness?

13:02.664 --> 13:05.546
We've all experienced the goodness of God.

13:05.566 --> 13:09.930
But at the same time, I do know that some of us, maybe many of us, still have questions.

13:10.511 --> 13:15.616
And I want to hit this head on here in week number one, is that there are often questions about the goodness of God.

13:16.797 --> 13:20.100
If God is good, and here's the big question, why?

13:20.140 --> 13:22.102
If God is good, why?

13:22.122 --> 13:23.483
And I just wrote down, these are just a few.

13:23.543 --> 13:30.770
Maybe you're here today, and you're in relationship with Jesus, and you're asking these questions, or if you're here today, and you're not in that personal relationship,

13:30.946 --> 13:33.350
Likely you have some of these or other questions.

13:33.930 --> 13:35.292
Why does God allow pain?

13:35.653 --> 13:36.895
Why doesn't He stop wickedness?

13:37.195 --> 13:38.377
Why eternal judgment?

13:38.397 --> 13:39.078
Why hell?

13:39.479 --> 13:40.981
Why can His people do bad things?

13:41.602 --> 13:44.226
Why disasters like earthquakes flood or cancer or war?

13:45.067 --> 13:48.432
And ultimately, bad things happen to good people.

13:48.492 --> 13:53.199
And if you have questions, almost the time out here, you just need to know God can handle your questions.

13:54.461 --> 13:57.746
Nowhere in the Bible does the Bible teach us not to ask questions?

13:58.434 --> 14:00.116
Jesus is the perfect example of this.

14:00.156 --> 14:03.159
He was a rabbi, which is really another way to say teacher.

14:03.740 --> 14:05.762
The key is that we bring those questions to Him.

14:06.563 --> 14:07.344
Can I get an amen?

14:08.165 --> 14:09.607
So bring those questions to Him.

14:09.667 --> 14:18.837
And I have a story of just a family here in our church that just exemplifies really everything I'm teaching today about walking through tough things, but still knowing the goodness of God in the middle of it.

14:19.578 --> 14:24.984
And it's the Wood family, Tony and Debbie Wood, who I got connected to in a moment of tragedy.

14:25.004 --> 14:26.386
This is about 11 years ago.

14:26.690 --> 14:31.797
